Fangren Marauder: "\"The fangren fight without comfort of any kind. We can ask no less of ourselves.\" --Tilien, Sylvok partisan"
Farbog Boneflinger: "\"Here are some bones for you to choke on, dear brother!\" --Gisa, to Geralf"
Farseek: "\"How truly vast this city must be, that I have traveled so far and seen so much, yet never once found the place where the buildings fail.\""
Farsight Mask: "It turns the adversity of the moment into the knowledge of a lifetime."
Favor of the Woods: "Feeling abandoned by Avacyn, some Kessigers turned to the pagan rituals of their ancestors."
Feast of Blood: "\"The vampires of this world don't know the pleasures of hunger. They gorge themselves without savoring the kill.\" --Sorin Markov"
Feast of the Unicorn: "\"Some delicacies are not to be savored, save by the callous.\" --Baron Sengir"
Feeding Frenzy: "It wasn't as much a strategy as a dim instinct to drown their prey."
Feral Hydra: "It shreds its prey as each head fights for the choicest bits."
Ferrovore: "The Vulshok use its digestion to break down the most obstinate metals, from darksteel myr to seastrider plates."
Fervent Cathar: "\"I'll put my sword down only to die. And I don't plan on doing that today.\""
Festering Goblin: "In life, it was a fetid, disease-ridden thing. In death, not much changed."
Fiery Hellhound: "There's nothing more exciting than a game of fetch the still-beating heart."
Final Punishment: "The pain of a lifetime--every scrape, illness, and bruise--condensed into a single moment."
Fire Elemental: "\"Fire set free is a fearsome force--destructive, merciless, always hungry. Given direction, it is much worse.\" --Jeflin, Vastwood shaman"
Firebreathing: "The mage breathed in life-giving air and breathed out death-bringing fire."
Fires of Undeath: "\"I drink of those who are worthy of my palate. The rest I burn.\""
Flameblast Dragon: "He marks his territory with fire and wrath, etching the mountainside with his charring breath."
Flameborn Hellion: "\"The most reliable omen of a future hellion attack is a past hellion attack.\" --Spear-Tribe teaching"
Flash Foliage: "\"This undemanding vegetation takes root in a mote of dust but grows incredibly quickly.\" --Simic research notes"
Flashfreeze: "\"Is cold merely the absence of heat, or a force unto itself? Would a display of its power help you decide?\" --Zubarek, Icewinder Magus"
Fledgling Griffin: "\"We're making progress, but its desire to explore still far exceeds its ability.\" --Amadi, Halimar griffin-master"
Fleeting Distraction: "The first spell taught to young mages, it has spared the lives of many whose hands are too small to hold a sword."
Flight: "\"Those who claim to know the world in its entirety rarely have the requisite perspective.\" --Ulmarus the Wise"
Fling: "The juiciest prey is that which grows lazy, thinking itself beyond the reach of danger."
Flinthoof Boar: "Through the smoke and flames it hunts, sniffing out the panicked and confused."
Fog: "It's hard enough to find your way through uncharted wilderness when you can see the tip of your nose."
Folk of An-Havva: "\"This town's only for good folk. The rest can go to the city.\" --Joskun, An-Havva Constable"
Foresee: "Two eyes to see what could be, two eyes to see what will."
Forge Devil: "Devils infiltrated the lower levels of Thraben Cathedral, making cracks in load-bearing pillars and setting fire to precious archives."
Forgotten Ancient: "Its blood is life. Its body is growth."
Fortress Crab: "Unbreakable and unappetizing, the crab grows uninterrupted, sometimes to the size of a cottage and beyond."
Fractured Powerstone: "The Thran learned to capture mana, but power inevitably escapes its bonds."
Frantic Salvage: "\"We will mourn when there is time. For now, we survive.\""
Frightful Delusion: "Whether he actually exists is in question, but the terror she feels is excruciatingly real."
Frost Breath: "If you have to be stuck somewhere for a while, it's better to be stuck there with a friend."
Fuel for the Cause: "\"Your ideas will be discarded and your will repurposed.\""
Fugitive Wizard: "Many wizards came to the Riptide Project hoping to return home with answers. Most, however, wouldn't return home at all."
Fulgent Distraction: "\"Channeling the white-hot power of all five suns creates a pretty good diversion.\" --Yavash of the Accorders"
Full Moon's Rise: "Some lycanthropes wish they could abandon their weak human shapes and revel in the power of the wolf."
Funeral Pyre: "\"Raze the body. Raise the soul.\" --Mystic elder"
Furyborn Hellkite: "\"Careful. A drop of blood here means death for us all.\" --Kalek, mountain guide"
Gaea's Might: "With the Heart of Yavimaya aiding him, Multani didn't even strain at the load."
Gallows Warden: "The spirit cares nothing for the crimes or triumphs of the slain. It shelters all beneath its stormy cloak."
Garruk's Packleader: "\"He has learned much in his long years. And unlike selfish humans, he's willing to share.\" --Garruk Wildspeaker"
Gatekeeper of Malakir: "\"You may enter the city--once the toll is paid.\""
Gather the Townsfolk: "In the memories of those they lost lies the strength needed to defend their city."
Gavony Ironwright: "\"I wish my work could shelter everyone, yet I pray we are never so few that it does.\""
Geistflame: "Innistrad pyromancers find their best raw materials in the fury of the dead."
Geosurge: "\"The mountains have been corrupted. Otherwise, they would not lend me their fire so easily.\" --Koth of the Hammer"
Geth's Verdict: "\"Everyone should owe you something.\" --Geth, Lord of the Vault"
Ghalma's Warden: "A special unit guards the loxodon artificer known as Ghalma the Shaper. They are armed and armored in her finest works of silver and steel."
Ghostly Flicker: "Sometimes it's useful to take a break from existence."
Ghoulcaller's Bell: "The bell's chime heralds the rise of the unhallowed from the grave and the fall of their victims into the earth."
Ghoulcaller's Chant: "\"The living are born small and weak. The dead rise ready to serve. The choice is obvious.\" --Gisa, ghoulcaller of Gavony"
Ghoulraiser: "\"Come. Bring your brothers. Tonight, you feast on living flesh.\" --Jadar, ghoulcaller of Nephalia"
Ghoultree: "It uproots entire fengrafs to add to its twisted frame."
Giant Scorpion: "Its sting hurts, but death is strangely painless."
Giant Spider: "\"The wild is always changing, but it does have a few constants.\" --Garruk Wildspeaker"
Gideon's Lawkeeper: "\"The essence of a lawful society is swift deterrence.\""
Gigantomancer: "\"All life is driven by an indomitable will to survive. I simply turn that into something more . . . tangible.\""
Gilded Lotus: "Over such beauty, wars are fought. With such power, wars are won."
Gitaxian Probe: "\"My flesh holds no secrets, monster. The spirit of Mirrodin will fight on.\" --Vy Covalt, Mirran resistance"
Gladecover Scout: "\"The forest is my cover and I hold it close. In such a tight embrace, there is no room for wickedness.\""
Glaze Fiend: "Before the zealots of the Ethersworn came to power, Esper illusionists dreamed up creations to mimic a variety of substances."
Gleemax: "Help us . . . R&D under mental domination of alien brain in jar . . . only chance . . . Gleemax's blatant disregard for flavor text . . . send help"
Glen Elendra Liege: "Those who displease Oona soon learn the extent of the armies she commands."
Glissa's Courier: "\"So, the survivors from Oxid Ridge are on the move. Let them come and witness predation in its purest form.\" --Glissa"
Gloom Surgeon: "He roams the streets of Havengul seeking the sick and delirious so that he may cure them of their lives."
Gloomhunter: "Scavengers both mundane and magical follow in its wake, feeding on the scraps of flesh and spirit it leaves behind."
Gloomwidow: "The abandoned towns on the moors didn't stay empty for long."
Glorious Charge: "\"One's blade is only as sharp as one's conviction.\" --Ajani Goldmane"
Glory Seeker: "The turning of the tide always begins with one soldier's decision to head back into the fray."
Glowering Rogon: "A herd of one."
Glowrider: "\"It is not yet time.\""
Gluttonous Zombie: "Greed and gluttony led him to death. Now they are his greatest assets."
Gnathosaur: "Mirran creatures that could withstand the Phyrexian oil found an abundance of crunchy snacks."
Go for the Throat: "Having flesh is increasingly a liability on Mirrodin."
Goblin Arsonist: "With great power comes great risk of getting yourself killed."
Goblin Assassin: "The more victims he kills, the more likely he is to get the right one."
Goblin Balloon Brigade: "\"The enemy is getting too close! Quick! Inflate the toad!\""
Goblin Chariot: "The hardest part of his training is learning not to eat the boar."
Goblin Digging Team: "\"Dig. Dig. Dig. Dig. Dig. Dig. Die\" --Goblin chant"
Goblin Firebug: "Most goblins leave behind a wake of destruction. A few goblins take one with them."
Goblin Fireslinger: "A rock between your eyes hurts. A burning rock between your eyes ruins your whole day."
Goblin Gardener: "Years of attempts have brought the goblins no closer to growing a sausage tree."
Goblin Glider: "\"What's got two arms, one wing, and no brains?\" --Ghitu riddle"
Goblin Grenade: "Don't underestimate the aerodynamic qualities of the common goblin."
Goblin King: "To be king, Numsgil did in Blog, who did in Unkful, who did in Viddle, who did in Loll, who did in Alrok. . . ."
Goblin Piker: "Once he'd worked out which end of the thing was sharp, he was promoted to guard duty."
Goblin Raider: "He's smart for a goblin. He can do two things: hit and run."
Goblin Roughrider: "Astride the bucking creature, Gribble hurtled down the mountainside while his Grotag brethren cheered. It was at that moment that legend of the Skrill Tamer was born."
Goblin Shortcutter: "\"Goblins are cheap, but be careful. It's a lot easier to steal from a corpse than a customer.\" --Samila, Murasa Expeditionary House"
Goblin Taskmaster: "For some reason, goblin fighting school isn't as crowded on day two."
Goblin Tunneler: "\"The best way over the mountain is through.\""
Goblin War Paint: "\"The secret to our war paint is hot peppers and stinkbugs. Lots of stinkbugs.\" --Skab, goblin secretkeeper"
Goblin Wardriver: "\"A true warrior fights with whatever's handy.\" --Qerk of the Secret Warren"
Gold Myr: "The myr are like razorgrass: numberless metal figures, reflecting each other's light."
Goldenglow Moth: "\"Little moth, fluttering bright, What luck will you bring tonight?\" --Benalish children's rhyme"
Goldnight Commander: "\"One faith, but many hands in victory.\""
Goldnight Redeemer: "The Host sings of Avacyn's return without a single verse about its own suffering."
Gorehorn Minotaurs: "Some of the eleven minotaur clans of Mirtiin are expert crafters and learned philosophers. Others just like to hit stuff."
Grasp of Darkness: "On a world with five suns, night is compelled to become an aggressive force."
Grassland Crusader: "\"Everyone deserves a chance to live. My job is to make sure they get it.\""
Gratuitous Violence: "Only the Cabal could make a fight to the death more deadly."
Grave Bramble: "Nature abhors a zombie."
Graveborn Muse: "\"Her voice is damnation, unyielding and certain.\" --Phage the Untouchable"
Gravecrawler: "\"Innistrad's ghoulcallers are talented enough, but let me show you what someone with real power can create.\" --Liliana Vess"
Gravedigger: "His grim ritual ushers the dead to their new life."
Gravepurge: "\"The Blessed Sleep? Ha! Wake up my lovelies, there's work to be done!\" --Gisa, ghoulcaller of Gavony"
Graveyard Shovel: "Thanks to Havengul's thriving illegal market for corpses, the shovel that interred a body during the day is usually the same one digging it out at night."
Greater Basilisk: "Bone, stone . . . both taste the same to a hungry basilisk."
Greater Werewolf: "\"The wolf-things are no mere beasts, but the lieutenants of the Baron.\" --Taysir"
Greatsword: "The only blow that matters is the killing blow."
Green Sun's Zenith: "As the green sun crowned, Phyrexian prophecies glowed on the Tree of Tales."
Greenweaver Druid: "The other tribes call them fanatics, but none deny that the Mul Daya elves have an iron-strong bond to some force greater than themselves."
Griffin Rider: "After fighting alongside the griffin riders, older knights of Thune learned to admire a mount that could rip an enemy to shreds in seconds."
Griffin Sentinel: "Once a griffin sentinel adopts a territory as its own, only death can force it to betray its post."
Grim Affliction: "Even the small wounds let hope bleed out."
Grim Discovery: "Few among the living understand just how much of their world is shaped by the ruins of the dead."
Grim Flowering: "\"Nothing in nature goes to waste, not even the rotting corpse of a good-for-nothing, blood-sucking vampire.\" --Halana of Ulvenwald"
Grixis Panorama: "There is no height above Grixis that is free from the stench of death."
Guard Duty: "\"I was told these were standard issue. Do I look standard to you?\""
Guard Gomazoa: "It lingers near the outposts of the Makindi Trenches, inadvertently granting another layer of defense."
Guardians of Akrasa: "\"Only by the bravery of those who put loyalty above glory is our home kept safe.\" --Elspeth Tirel"
Guardians' Pledge: "A dozen fighting for each other are worth a thousand fighting for themselves."
Gust-Skimmer: "Phyrexian smog clouds choked the skies, threatening creatures who couldn't comprehend the menace below."
Gustcloak Runner: "Cabal spies trying to follow the Order's movements are constantly frustrated by tracks that stop dead."
Gut Shot: "\"Down here, we have a more pointed version of the scriptures.\" --Urabrask's enforcer"
Hamlet Captain: "\"I would fear this fight, bloodsucker, were I alone.\""
Hanweir Watchkeep: "He scans for wolves, knowing there's one he can never anticipate."
Harbor Serpent: "Like most giant monsters villagers worship as gods, it proves a fickle master."
Harm's Way: "Even when fate is already written, there's always time to change the names."
Harmonize: "\"Words lie. People lie. The land tells the truth.\""
Harrow: "The Roil redraws the world as it passes, leaving only the hedrons unchanged."
Harrowing Journey: "\"There are always fools who attempt to traverse Kruin Pass before sundown and every time they wind up in a race for their lives.\" --Old Rutstein"
Harvest Pyre: "Corpses destroyed by fire form the most destructive geists."
Haunted Fengraf: "A ghoulcaller's playground."
Havengul Runebinder: "\"So many corpses, so little time.\""
Headless Skaab: "A head is a needless encumbrance when muscle is all that's required."
Heat Ray: "\"There was clearly a scream. I'm not sure if there was a mouth.\" --Sachir, Akoum Expeditionary House"
Hedron Crab: "\"I don't care when the hedrons awoke. Why is the question that really matters.\" --Anowon, the Ruin Sage"
Hellkite Igniter: "Its flight sets the sky itself on fire."
Heroes' Reunion: "\"You helped save my people from a Phyrexian fate. Did you think I wouldn't return the favor?\" --Eladamri, to Gerrard"
Hexplate Golem: "\"Use everything. Iron, rust, scrap . . . even the ground must join our cause.\" --Ezuri, renegade leader"
Hideous Visage: "\"Seeing you cower before me is its own reward.\""
Highborn Ghoul: "\"All the dead sleep lightly here, no matter how refined their beds may be.\" --Grafdigger Wulmer"
Highland Berserker: "He gets paid by the axe."
Hindering Light: "Centuries of careful practice have elevated the casting of protective spells to an art form. What little offensive magic remains on Bant stands little chance of breaching them."
Hinterland Harbor: "In places where the sea meets the trees, it's easy to forget the darkness that rules most of Innistrad."
Hinterland Hermit: "He tried to live far from those he could hurt . . ."
Hoard-Smelter Dragon: "He collects the precious metals, and then converts the rest to propellant."
Hollowhenge Beast: "In a world of monsters, it's the stuff of nightmares."
Hollowhenge Spirit: "Some spirits mourn. Others terrorize."
Holy Strength: "\"Born under the moon, the second child will stumble on temptation and seek power in the dark places of the heart.\" --Codex of the Constellari"
Horned Turtle: "It's a mistake to say turtles hide in their shells. They merely need time to contemplate how best to bite your head off."
Hornet Sting: "It was only then--to his infinite sorrow--that Gork realized hornets don't make honey."
Hovermyr: "Originally created to harvest blinkmoths, the hovermyr are now the silent observers of a dying world."
Hunter Sliver: "Once they get the scent, there is no escape."
Hunter's Insight: "\"The predator knows the true way of the world. Life is conflict. Only the strong survive.\" --Garruk Wildspeaker"
Hunters' Feast: "Those who kill a jawspur rhino must prepare spells to lift the carcass--even a dozen hunters can't lift its bulk."
Ichor Wellspring: "\"Our glorious infection has taken hold.\" --Elesh Norn, Grand Cenobite"
Illusionary Servant: "\"Illusion is a handy but fragile medium. Use it only in a pinch, or against the dim-witted.\" --Jace Beleren"
Immolating Souleater: "\"We thank the souleaters for melting the sinful that we may be reminded of our own insignificance.\" --Drones' hymn of gratitude"
Incinerate: "\"Spontaneous combustion is a myth. If you burst into flame, someone wanted you to.\" --Chandra Nalaar"
Indrik Stomphowler: "\"An indrik's howl has destructive power much subtler than that of its crushing foot. The sound is mundane, but inaudible vibrations scatter and sunder magical contrivances.\" --Simic research notes"
Induce Despair: "All the angel saw was her doom."
Infantry Veteran: "\"Any fool can pick up a sword and charge into battle. To emerge alive at the end, that is a gift that comes from leadership and experience.\""
Infiltration Lens: "Neurok spies carry devices that let them look a few moments into the future, giving them an almost insurmountable edge."
Inkfathom Witch: "The murk of the Wanderbrine concealed unseemly rituals designed to bring out the worst in merrowkind."
Inspired Charge: "\"Impossible! How could they overwhelm us? We had barricades, war elephants, . . . and they were barely a tenth of our number!\" --General Avitora"
Instill Infection: "\"The results of our ninth inoculation were the same. The specimen was, of course, euthanized before the contagion could spread.\" --Vedalken research notes"
Intangible Virtue: "In life, they were a motley crew: farmers, lords, cutpurses, priests. In death, they are united in singular, benevolent purpose."
Into the Core: "\"They believe they're driving us back, but we're leading them to their doom.\" --Kethek, furnace stoker"
Into the Maw of Hell: "Few entrances lead to where demons and devils lurk. Unfortunately, they occasionally open new ones."
Iona's Judgment: "Beneath the gaze of angels, only the righteous may stand without fear."
Iron Myr: "The myr are like rusted metal: gleaming purpose hidden by a thin disguise of debris."
Jace's Erasure: "\"You should try to clear your mind of idle thoughts. And if you can't, I will.\""
Jace's Ingenuity: "\"Brute force can sometimes kick down a locked door, but knowledge is a skeleton key.\""
Jade Mage: "\"We are one with the wild things. Life blooms from our fingertips and nature responds to our summons.\" --Jade creed"
Jagwasp Swarm: "\"You know how to tell a sapling explorer from an old hardhead? See which one mistakes a swarm of jagwasps for the setting sun.\" --Chadir the Navigator"
Jayemdae Tome: "A true scribe devotes an entire lifetime to the creation of a single volume, a masterpiece as unique as its maker."
Joint Assault: "\"By my power, werewolves shall become the wolfir, our allies in combat against darkness.\" --Avacyn's Cursemute Decree"
Jwari Scuttler: "\"Yeah, they've got a lot of meat. The only downside to eating 'em is that you often find human bones and body parts inside.\" --Jaby, Silundi Sea nomad"
"Kamahl, Fist of Krosa": "\"My mind has changed. My strength has not.\""
Kavu Recluse: "Few ever see this particular breed of kavu, which hides in forests of its own making."
Kavu Scout: "The kavu evolved for centuries deep inside Dominaria, and some can draw from its strength."
Keeneye Aven: "\"I have no need of a map. The very continent itself guides my way.\""
Kelinore Bat: "The nesting bats of Kelinore sleep soundly while the sun passes, nestled among their grisly collections."
Kemba's Skyguard: "\"We're now to dispense aid to any Mirran we see battling anything . . . ‘strange.' Regent's orders.\" --Ranya, skyhunter captain"
Kessig Wolf: "When a werewolf changes for the first time, that first howl is said to echo through the wilds till moonset."
Kessig Wolf Run: "When a werewolf changes for the first time, that first howl is said to echo through the wilds till moonset."
Kite Shield: "\"To my sword I owe my glory, but to my shield I owe my life.\" --Sarlena, paladin of the Northern Verge"
Kitesail: "Carving lines through the sky, kite sailors map trails for the pilgrims below to follow."
Knight of Glory: "\"I will uphold the law, and no manner of foe will stop me.\""
Knight of the Hokey Pokey: "That's what it's all about."
Kor Firewalker: "\"A river of lava is just another river to cross.\""
Kor Hookmaster: "\"For us, a rope represents the ties that bind the kor. For you, it's more literal.\""
Kor Outfitter: "\"We take only what we need to survive. Believe me, you will need this.\""
Kor Sanctifiers: "\"Why keep such trinkets? They only add weight to your travels.\""
Koth's Courier: "Koth sent partisans into the Tangle to bring survivors to the safe haven of the tunnels below Kuldotha."
Kraken's Eye: "It's seen the wonders of entire worlds trapped in the depths of a bottomless ocean."
Krosan Constrictor: "\"It's a slithering, coldblooded menace. I've gotta respect that.\" --Braids, dementia summoner"
Krosan Drover: "\"Sit.\""
Krosan Wayfarer: "\"The Krosan Forest lives, and druids are its seeds.\" --Seton, centaur druid"
Kuldotha Rebirth: "All goblin rituals serve a dual purpose as fertility rites, even the destructive ones. Especially the destructive ones."
Kuldotha Ringleader: "Being surrounded by goblins is less objectionable when they're fighting for you."
Kurgadon: "When it walks through Krosa, trees step aside, leaves take wing, and the ground shudders."
Last Kiss: "\"Romanticize it, glamorize it, call it what you will. To me, it will always be carnal, bloody murder.\" --Ayli, Kamsa cleric"
Lava Axe: "It can chop down a redwood in a single stroke. Your sternum isn't going to fare any better."
Lavafume Invoker: "\"Then the ancient masters themselves, towers of rapacity, rose and began their calamitous feast.\" --The Invokers' Tales"
Leaden Myr: "The myr are like necrogen: a transformative force unconcerned with the changes they wreak."
Leaf Arrow: "\"Those who think the trees shall remain bystanders throughout this conflict shall be sorely mistaken.\" --Sutina, Speaker of the Tajuru"
Leaf Gilder: "Eidren, perfect of Lys Alana, ordered hundreds of trees uprooted and rearranged into a pattern he deemed beautiful. Thus the Gilt-Leaf Wood was born."
Leaping Lizard: "\"I never question the Autumn Willow about her motives, not even when she turns people into Lizards. It's her way.\" --Devin, Faerie Noble"
Leatherback Baloth: "Heavy enough to withstand the Roil, leatherback skeletons are havens for travelers in storms and landshifts."
Leonin Skyhunter: "\"The infection has spread farther than we could glimpse from the heights of Taj-Nar.\""
Lifelink: "The spoils of war are not measured only in gold and silver."
Lightning Blast: "\"I'll climb down soon. Don't worry, it's just a thundersto--\" --Former elvish scout"
Lightning Elemental: "\"Oh, it's easy enough to kill, but I'm not going anywhere near it.\" --Norin the Wary"
Liliana's Specter: "\"The finest minions know what I need without me ever saying a thing.\" --Liliana Vess"
Lingering Souls: "The murdered inhabitants of Hollowhenge impart to the living the terror they felt in death."
Living Tsunami: "At low tide it slumbers. At high tide it devours."
Llanowar Elves: "One bone broken for every twig snapped underfoot. --Llanowar penalty for trespassing"
Lone Missionary: "His mission has become a grim pilgrimage, a tour of the Eldrazi-stricken outposts across Zendikar. But he marches on alone, stubborn as the daily dawn."
Looming Shade: "Its form never rests, propelled by some undetectable gale from beyond the gloom."
Lord of the Unreal: "\"The dream does not end until I say so.\""
Lost in the Mist: "The secrets she carried could have saved many lives, but they quietly drowned with her."
Lowland Tracker: "\"I feed my hatred to the righteous and they join my crusade.\" --Akroma, angelic avenger"
Loxodon Partisan: "\"This war is not about loxodon or leonin, Sylvok or Auriok. To defeat these rotters, we must do it together.\""
Loxodon Wayfarer: "The Mirran elders vanished with Memnarch, leaving behind a generation of wayward orphans."
Loyal Cathar: "\"I trust myself to do my duty, even unto death. It's what comes after that I'm afraid of.\" --Constable Visil, to Thalia"
Lumberknot: "Animated by geists fused in its oak, it hungers for more life to add to its core."
Lumengrid Drake: "Properly outfitted, drakes made perfect sentries for vedalken strongholds."
Lure: "It makes the insignificant conspicuous, the repulsive alluring, and the deadly irresistible."
Macetail Hystrodon: "The goblins tracked the hystrodon with much stealth and cunning. Then they were eaten with much pain and yelling."
Magma Rift: "\"Lighting a fire needs kindling and heat. You be the kindling. I'll bring the heat.\" --Chandra Nalaar"
Mahamoti Djinn: "Of royal blood among the spirits of the air, the Mahamoti djinn rides on the wings of the winds. As dangerous in the gambling hall as he is in battle, he is a master of trickery and misdirection."
Makindi Griffin: "As the hedrons began to coalesce into colossal Eldrazi superstructures, the griffins were forced to seek new territory lest their aeries be crushed between the massive stone monoliths."
Mana Leak: "The fatal flaw in every plan is the assumption that you know more than your enemy."
Manalith: "Planeswalkers seek out great monuments throughout the Multiverse, knowing that their builders were unknowingly drawn by the convergence of mana in the area."
Manic Vandal: "It's fun. He doesn't need another reason."
Marisi's Twinclaws: "\"Looks like we're completely outnumbered.\" \"Lucky for us. I thought we'd be bored.\""
Markov Warlord: "\"What use is a stake or holy symbol in the hands of a coward?\""
Mask of Avacyn: "It hides the face and protects the soul."
Master Thief: "Possession is ten-tenths of the law."
Master's Call: "The need to obey was inscribed on every plate in their bodies."
Melira's Keepers: "Her warriors are the last defense against the coming storm."
Memnite: "Reminders of Memnarch's reign still skirr across Mirrodin, reminiscent of his form if not his power."
Mental Note: "Some minds are more open than others."
Merfolk Looter: "Merfolk don't always know what they're looking for, but they're certain once they find it."
Merfolk Mesmerist: "\"Don't you think if I saw a half-woman, half-fish with three glowing eyes, I'd have remembered?\" --Drugo, town guard"
Mesa Chicken: "\"Lo! lord of layers proudly comb-crested Hero to hens father to feathers Crowing sun-caller weaver of wattle Elder to eggs.\" --Rooster Saga"
Mesa Enchantress: "\"Scholars seek to understand the way the world is. I wish to shape the world into what it should be.\""
Midvast Protector: "\"I cultivated my faith in Avacyn despite meager returns. Now my faith is repaid.\""
Might of the Masses: "The Joraga elves never need ask a troll to leave their territory. They merely grant it their combined strength, and it can't resist embarking on a merry rampage."
Mighty Leap: "\"The southern fortress taken by invaders? Heh, sure . . . when elephants fly.\" --Brezard Skeinbow, captain of the guard"
Mind Control: "\"Every primitive mind has a motive. Easy to find, and eminently exploitable.\" --Noyan Dar, Tazeem lullmage"
Mind Rot: "\"What a pity. You should have written it down.\" --Liliana Vess"
Mind Sludge: "\"Guard your thoughts. You never know who might wish to take them from you.\" --Kalitas, Bloodchief of Ghet"
Mind Spring: "Fragments of thought refract and multiply, surging in a geyser of dizzying insight."
Mind Unbound: "The creations of the hand are confined by reality. The creations of the mind know no such limits."
Mindbreak Trap: "\"Life is a maze. This is one of its dead ends.\" --Noyan Dar, Tazeem lullmage"
Mindcrank: "\"Let go of your memories and be reborn.\" --Argent Etchings, plate 106, passage 27"
Mire Blight: "\"Is there anything in Guul Draz that doesn't suck the life out of you?\" --Tarsa, Sea Gate sell-sword"
Mirran Crusader: "A symbol of what Mirrodin once was and hope for what it will be again."
Mirran Mettle: "\"Our land will not yield to Phyrexian corruption!\""
Mirran Spy: "Accurate information is a precious commodity in times of war."
Mist Raven: "\"When you see a raven, head for the hills. It knows when the ghost-tide is headed in.\" --Sved, fisherman of Nephalia"
Mistform Sliver: "Taking the form of a junior researcher, the first sliver slipped out of Riptide."
Mitotic Manipulation: "\"They can't even comprehend nature. How could they improve it?\" --Venser"
Mogg Flunkies: "They'll attack whatever's in front of them--as long as you tell them where that is."
Molder Beast: "\"A trail of scrap metal can lead it into an ambush. But take care not to overfeed it.\" --Adaran, Tangle hunter"
"Molimo, Maro-Sorcerer": "\"My mind is the spread of the canopy. My heart is the embrace of the roots. I am deathless Llanowar, its fury and its peace.\""
Moment of Heroism: "\"My faith is stronger than fang, claw, or mindless hunger.\""
Moon Heron: "The heron is the symbol of the archangel Avacyn. The fact that such spirits still fly gives the church hope that its founder may one day return."
Moorland Inquisitor: "Inquisitors are taught scripture, philosophy, and the fine art of sharpening an axe."
Morality Shift: "The mind sings, though at times it sings a dirge."
Morbid Bloom: "\"From the damned I make my garden.\" --Jorshu of Clan Nel Toth"
Morbid Plunder: "Even the dead are raw materials for the Phyrexian vision of perfection."
Mulch: "The land knows no difference between the graves of commoners and nobles."
Murder of Crows: "Even more than carrion, they crave the last words of the dying."
Mutagenic Growth: "\"Sympathy is for weaklings. Whoever survives, wins.\" --Benzir, archdruid of Temple Might"
Mycosynth Wellspring: "The oil created the mycosynth. The mycosynth created New Phyrexia."
Myr Galvanizer: "\"We can't quite determine what they're doing, but they seem to be doing it quite well.\" --Vedalken research notes"
Myr Sire: "For the Phyrexians, death is not an end, nor a one-time occurrence."
Myrsmith: "The Auriok see the artificer as a conduit, beckoning new creations into the world."
Mystic Familiar: "They soar, and the mystics follow."
Naturalize: "\"When your cities and trinkets crumble, only nature will remain.\" --Garruk Wildspeaker"
Nature's Spiral: "Snail shell, fern, tornado--the world connects all things in form."
Nearheath Stalker: "\"Do not speak of this to the elders. They look unfavorably upon my indulgences.\""
Negate: "Masters of the arcane savor a delicious irony. Their study of deep and complex arcana leads to such a simple end: the ability to say merely yes or no."
Nema Siltlurker: "In one gargantuan bite, it will swallow not only you but also the riverbank you were standing on."
Nephalia Drownyard: "\"Some see a coastal disaster. I see a fully-stocked seagraf.\" --Jadar, ghoulcaller of Nephalia"
Niblis of the Breath: "\"Why do the dead remain among us? Where is Flight Alabaster to lead them home? Where is Avacyn?\" --Eruth of Lambholt"
Niblis of the Mist: "\"Not even a roaring fire could thaw the chill it put in my heart.\" --Vonn, geist-trapper"
Niblis of the Urn: "\"I never had the nerve to open that bottle. I'll bet you're wishing right now you hadn't been so curious yourself.\" --Old Rutstein"
Night Revelers: "Vampires think of themselves as the indisputable nobility of Innistrad, able to do as they please. There are few who can prove them wrong."
Nightbird's Clutches: "Shiny polished silver can ward off many creatures, but it attracts others."
Nightwing Shade: "\"There is one hour of the night even we do not watch.\" --Sedva, captain of the watch"
Nissa's Chosen: "\"Nissa will save the elves, but only the ones who have proved their worth.\""
Noble Vestige: "Most spirits are chained to this world by their despair, but he remains tethered by his hope for better days."
"Novijen, Heart of Progress": "\"The unnatural pressures of life in this city are best withstood by lifeforms that adapt with unnatural swiftness.\" --Momir Vig"
Noxious Ghoul: "Plague and death wrapped in one convenient package."
Oakenform: "\"When the beast cloaks itself in the mighty oak, what good is a bow? When the oak wraps itself around the snarling beast, what good is a hatchet?\" --Dionus, elvish archdruid"
Oculus: "\"In its gaze I saw no mercy, no recognition that I was worthy to exist.\" --Kara Vrist, Neurok agent"
Offering to Asha: "\"His body belongs to Bant now. His soul? I honestly don't know. I expect it belongs to the angels.\" --Rafiq of the Many"
Ogre Resister: "He didn't have a word for \"home,\" but he knew it was something to be defended."
Ogre's Cleaver: "She adopted the weapon of the slave-lord Kazuul, and with it, all his cruelty."
Oran-Rief Survivalist: "\"I'm strong enough to survive alone. I'm smart enough to want companions at my side.\""
Ordered Migration: "\"Birds reach all parts of the world,\" said Barrin. \"They will make excellent scouts.\""
Ornithopter: "Regardless of the century, plane, or species, developing artificers never fail to invent the ornithopter."
Overgrown Battlement: "\"Our enemy is nothing less than the end of all life. We shall not want for allies.\" --The War Diaries"
Oxidda Scrapmelter: "It subsists on a diet rich in screaming metal and molten blood."
Pacifism: "For the first time in his life, Grakk felt a little warm and fuzzy inside."
Painful Quandary: "\"For each word spoken, one forgotten. For each thought, a memory rotten.\" --Moriok incantation"
Palace Guard: "\"I'm not nearly as bothered by being outnumbered as I am by their foul stench.\""
Palladium Myr: "The myr are like the Glimmervoid: blank canvases on which to build grand creations."
Panic Attack: "\"What do they see in the throes of panic? I'm not sure I want to know.\" --Kezim, prodigal pyromancer"
Paper Tiger: "The tiger is always quick to fold."
Paralyzing Grasp: "The Halimar Sea Caves are both the breeding ground of giant squids and the dumping ground of hardened criminals."
Paraselene: "\"Moonlight has a way of showing all things as they truly are--for better or for worse.\" --Zilla of Lambholt"
Patagia Golem: "Its wings were only designed to be ornamental, but it learned to use them on its own."
Peel from Reality: "\"Soulless demon, you are bound to me. Now we will both dwell in oblivion.\""
Pennon Blade: "Draped with the pennon of a fallen outpost, the sword came to symbolize the peoples of Zendikar becoming one."
Peregrine Griffin: "A griffin is not just an eagle's wings and a lion's claws. It is also the fiercest of hearts."
Perilous Myr: "To Mirrodin, an explosive. To Phyrexia, a missionary."
Personal Sanctuary: "\"There is a place deep within my soul where no foe can intrude and no tyrant can conquer.\" --Sarlena, paladin of the Northern Verge"
Phantasmal Bear: "\"You know it to be false, but when its claws find you, what you know won't matter much at all.\" --Pol Jamaar, illusionist"
Phantasmal Dragon: "Its hunger and ire are no less for being wrought of lies and mist."
Phantom Warrior: "The construction of a defense is not accomplished by adding bricks. -Jace Beleren"
Phyresis: "\"Perfection is at hand. You have been freed of weakness and made compleat.\" --Sheoldred, Whispering One"
Phyrexian Digester: "\"Our cause will ripen in the fertile flesh of the unworthy.\" --Sheoldred, Whispering One"
Phyrexian Hulk: "An invasion weapon of ages past, the glistening oil contained the blueprints of countless atrocities."
Phyrexian Juggernaut: "Where nature impedes, Phyrexians overcome."
Phyrexian Rager: "\"I believe many worlds will bow to Phyrexia. Mirrodin is merely the first.\" --Sheoldred, Whispering One"
Pierce Strider: "\"Pain isn't a negative stimulus. Pain is a sign of your imperfection.\" --Sheoldred, Whispering One"
Pilgrim's Eye: "The kor send their thopter kites to see if the land is in a welcoming mood."
Pillage: "\"Burn their homes. Salt their lands. Nothing survives.\" --The Western Paladin"
Pinpoint Avalanche: "\"Some solve problems by thinking and talking. Others use rocks.\" --Toggo, goblin weaponsmith"
Pistus Strike: "\"Even a nuisance such as the pistus fly has a purpose in our new world.\" --Glissa"
Pitchburn Devils: "The ingenuity of goblins, the depravity of demons, and the smarts of sheep."
Plague Myr: "They watch for a new master, one more sinister than the last."
Plaguemaw Beast: "Phyrexia's spiral of consumption grows ever wider and darker."
Planar Guide: "\"Every moment has its own savior.\""
Plated Geopede: "\"Kor armorers buy the scales and claws. Elf oracles buy the rest.\" --Nablus, North Hada trapper"
Plated Seastrider: "The Neurok buried entangling cables just under the Quicksilver Sea. One seastrider harvest can provide an army's worth of armor and shields."
Plated Sliver: "Overcoming extinction has only made the slivers more determined to live."
Platinum Angel: "She is the apex of the artificer's craft, the spirit of the divine called out of base metal."
Plummet: "\"Let nothing own the skies but the wind.\" --Dejara, Giltwood druid"
Ponder: "Tomorrow belongs to those who prepare for it today."
Praetor's Counsel: "As the Phyrexian contagion corroded Karn's body, the praetors whispered psalms to corrupt his mind."
Prey Upon: "\"You don't find many old werewolf hunters.\" --Paulin, trapper of Somberwald"
Pride Guardian: "\"Any hotheaded cub can raise a sword in anger.\""
Priests of Norn: "\"May our blessings sever the tongues of the forsaken.\" --Elesh Norn, Grand Cenobite"
Prized Unicorn: "\"The desire for its magic horn inspires such bloodthirsty greed that all who see the unicorn will kill to possess it.\" --Dionus, elvish archdruid"
Prodigal Pyromancer: "\"What am I looking at? Ashes, dead man.\""
Profane Prayers: "\"We have ways to make you talk, but you have nothing interesting to say.\""
Protean Hulk: "\"Meat and eggs. We eat!\" --Borborygmos"
Psychic Miasma: "\"A mind may be steeled against madness, but all battlements fall in time.\" --Jin-Gitaxias, Core Augur"
Psychosis Crawler: "\"If that brain can't figure out the secret of the serum, then add more brains.\" --Rhmir, Hand of the Augur"
Pulse Tracker: "Pulse trackers terrorize adventurers, driving them through the jungle toward certain death at the gates of Malakir."
Puncturing Light: "\"The vampires knew what was coming. I know it. And they did nothing. They deserve to feel the same agony they've caused all of us.\" --Anitan, Ondu cleric"
Purify the Grave: "Some priests speak in whispers of the Helvault, a silver prison of unpurged evils."
Pyretic Ritual: "The Multiverse is filled with limitless power just waiting for someone to reach out and seize it."
Quag Sickness: "The dread gases didn't kill Farbid. But as he lay in the muck, miserable and helpless, watching ghouls and rats advance on him, he wished they had."
Quick Sliver: "The directors of the Riptide Project wanted instant results on the sliver experiments. They got their wish."
Quicksilver Geyser: "\"Phyrexians are tenacious. That's not the same thing as clever.\" --Tezzeret"
Quilled Slagwurm: "Vorinclex removed its teeth so it wouldn't waste time chewing before moving to the next kill."
Quirion Dryad: "\"Never underestimate the ability of natural forces to adapt to unnatural influences.\" --Molimo, maro-sorcerer"
Quirion Explorer: "Fight with a friend at your back, steel in your hands, and magic in your veins. --Quirion creed"
Quirion Trailblazer: "\"All that matters is the path ahead.\""
Rage Extractor: "New Phyrexia is an engine that both consumes and creates malice."
Rage Thrower: "\"Some lament these haunted times, but I'm a geistflame-tank-half-full kind of person.\""
Raging Goblin: "He raged at the world, at his family, at his life. But mostly he just raged."
Raid Bombardment: "Goblins in the first wave of a fire raid always bemoan the aim of everyone else."
Rain of Blades: "Some say they are the weapons of heroes fallen in battle, eager for one last chance at glory."
Rally the Forces: "\"Drive them back! Make their underworld into their grave!\" --Koth of the Hammer"
Rampant Growth: "Nature grows solutions to its problems."
Rancor: "Hatred outlives the hateful."
Ranger's Guile: "In the remote corners of Kessig, protection is found in secret powers unknown to the Church of Avacyn."
Ranger's Path: "The forest can seem like a dense maze. Those who travel the canopy know otherwise."
Razor Hippogriff: "She incubates her eggs in gold and mana."
Razorfield Rhino: "Adapted to tread on razorgrass, the rhino proved adept at treading on Phyrexians as well."
Razorfield Thresher: "DANGER! Keep appendages clear of front of machine. And rear of machine. And side of machine. And top of machine."
Reassembling Skeleton: "\"They may show up with the wrong thigh bone or mandible, but they always show up.\" --Zul Ashur, lich lord"
Rebuke: "\"No one chooses to be stitched together into a skaab. If it could speak, it would beg for its own destruction.\" --Thalia, Knight-Cathar"
Reckless Brute: "His mind knows no fear, registering only the burning impulse to destroy."
Reckless Scholar: "\"Any good prospector must sift the gold from the sand.\""
Reclaim: "The wise pay as much attention to what they throw away as to what they keep."
Redirect: "\"It's actually quite simple, but since you've only recently begun to walk upright, it may take some time to explain.\" --Jace Beleren, to Garruk Wildspeaker"
Relic Putrescence: "\"Until we shed the curse of sentience, we must endure its grotesque handiwork.\" --Vorinclex, Voice of Hunger"
Reliquary Tower: "Once guarded by the Knights of the Reliquary, the tower stands now protected only by its own remoteness, its dusty treasures open to plunder by anyone."
Repel the Darkness: "A boon to those who cannot see in the dark. A bane to those who live in it."
Revive: "Even what is lost beyond recall returns when coaxed by a dryad's hand."
Revoke Existence: "\"No half measures, no regrets. We'll tell no stories of this day. It will be as if it never existed at all.\" --Ganedor, loxodon mystic"
Reward the Faithful: "\"When you have drunk your fill, pass the cup to others who thirst.\""
Righteous Blow: "\"Monsters will no longer find safety under the mists of Morkrut!\" --Bruna, Light of Alabaster"
Righteous Cause: "\"Until the world unites in vengeful fury and Phage is destroyed, I will not stay my hand.\" --Akroma, angelic avenger"
Rites of Flourishing: "\"Dance, and bring forth the coil! It is an umbilical to Gaea herself, fattening us with the earth's rich bounty.\""
River Boa: "\"Sheath your swords! Cudgels only. I see a new pair of waterproof trek boots slithering away.\" --Nablus, North Hada trapper"
Roc Egg: "A thin shell lies between the roc and a world of bite-sized treats."
Rock Lobster: "Many take the lobster for granite."
Rolling Temblor: "When demons open a path to your front door, it's time to move."
Root Sliver: "\"It would take another apocalypse to stop the slivers now.\" --Riptide Project researcher"
Rotted Hystrix: "Vorinclex had no grand plan. The oil did its own work, evolving creatures into worthy predators."
Rotting Fensnake: "Its venom sacs are long gone, but its crushing strength is somehow greater than ever."
Rotting Legion: "Zombies have one speed: shamble."
Rune-Scarred Demon: "The litany of the infernal on his flesh pulses to the beating of his dark heart."
Runeclaw Bear: "The only honey it wants is the sweet nectar flowing through your veins."
Runic Repetition: "\"What some call obsession, I call the quest for perfection.\""
Rusted Relic: "\"We consider rust a curable disease.\" --Tarrin, Hammer-Tribe shaman"
Rusted Sentinel: "It has to deliberate a moment on the best way to break your face."
Rusted Slasher: "\"It's a beautiful vision. Discarded debris is reborn as a singular entity.\" --Urabrask the Hidden"
Ruthless Invasion: "\"For the survival of our people, every conflict must now end in retreat.\" --Pythor, Mirran resistance"
Saberclaw Golem: "The warriors of the Blade Tribe charged the golem, twenty strong. They returned numbering ten . . . and a half."
Sacred Wolf: "\"I raised my bow, and the wolf stared at me. Under its gaze, my finger would not release the string.\" --Aref the Hunter"
Safe Passage: "As she shepherds the faithful, the angel's radiance is a shield of salvation."
Sages of the Anima: "Godtrackers found new pantheons of beast-gods beyond Naya's borders."
Sai of the Shinobi: "The passing of the sai presages the end of the old clan and the ascent of the new."
Sakura-Tribe Elder: "Slain orochi warriors were buried with a tree sapling so they would become a part of the forest after death."
Samite Alchemist: "\"Powders and potions are nothing compared to faith.\" --Baris, Serra Inquisitor"
Sanctuary Cat: "Cats prowl the corridors of Avacyn's churches in search of devils or signs of their mischief."
Sands of Delirium: "It counts down your last few moments of sanity."
Savage Silhouette: "Some elves believe that their survival instincts are born of many cycles of reincarnation."
Saving Grasp: "Nothing's more valuable than perfect timing."
Scalding Devil: "Demons massacre. Devils annoy."
Scepter of Empires: "\"With this scepter, smite your enemies.\" --Scepter inscription"
Scissors Lizard: "Nothing beats the lizard's shear power."
Scoria Elemental: "A single molten cord links it to the subterranean furnaces, drawing heat and metal from beneath Kuldotha. Until that bond is cut, it carves a swath of raw destruction."
Scourge of Geier Reach: "Stensian villagers mourned the loss of human life. Thraben vampire slayers mourned the loss of living wood."
Scourge Servant: "\"The union of the oil and necrogen has produced many pleasing reactions.\" --Sheoldred, Whispering One"
Scrapdiver Serpent: "Smart artificers clean up after themselves."
Screeching Skaab: "Its screeching is the sound of you losing your mind."
Scroll of Avacyn: "Words to bless the eye that reads them, telling of a future beyond the reach of fear."
Scroll Thief: "The arcane academies along the coast were powerless to protect themselves from the brazen raiders of the Kapsho Seas."
Scythe Tiger: "Instead of adapting to its environment, it adapts its environment to itself."
Sea Gate Oracle: "\"The secret entrance should be near.\""
Sea Sprite: "\"No one can catch what won't be caught.\" --Kakra, Sea Troll"
Seachrome Coast: "Where the Quicksilver Sea laps over the Razor Fields, the landscape reflects the suns' fading hope."
Seaside Citadel: "For wisdom's sake, it was built high to gaze on all things. For glory's sake, it was built high as a testament of power. For strength's sake, it was built high to repel all attacks."
Seismic Strike: "\"Life up here is simple. Adapt to the ways of the mountains and they will reward you. Fight them and they will end you.\" --Kezim, prodigal pyromancer"
Seize the Initiative: "The time between spotting a leonin shikari and feeling its claws is just time enough to draw your last breath."
Selfless Cathar: "\"If I fail to offer myself, we will surely be overrun. My fate would be the same.\""
Selhoff Occultist: "\"The mist whispers to those who know it to be more than a mundane fog.\""
Sengir Vampire: "Empires rise and fall, but evil is eternal."
Sensory Deprivation: "They call it \"stitcher's anesthesia,\" a spell to deaden the senses while the mad doctors begin their grisly work."
Seraph of Dawn: "She parts the clouds so sunlight can reach even the darkest lairs and duskiest tombs."
Serpent's Gift: "Venom is nature's way of redressing the imbalance between weak and mighty."
Serra Angel: "Follow the light. In its absence, follow her."
Serum Raker: "The serum from the blinkmoths they gather greases the joints of witch engines."
Severed Legion: "No one in Aphetto answers a knock at the door after sundown."
Sewn-Eye Drake: "\"Too wary to charge, too prudent to serve. Not anymore.\" --Sedris, the Traitor King"
Shatter: "\"I am an artist, a builder, a creator . . . I create the biggest explosions around.\" --Krol, goblin furnace-priest"
Shattered Perception: "\"You must shatter the fetters of the past. Only then can you truly act.\" --Rem Karolus, Blade of the Inquisitors"
Shepherd of Rot: "\"My priests swore loyalty to the Cabal not until death, but beyond it.\" --Cabal Patriarch"
Shepherd of the Lost: "\"Should you fall in the wilds, lift your voice to the Sky Realm. The one who answers will be your salvation.\" --Emeria's Creed"
Shieldmate's Blessing: "\"Even land dwellers may call for Emeria's grace in times of need.\" --Emeria's Creed"
Shimmering Grotto: "\"This is the price of being last in the food chain. We must keep our places of beauty hidden away instead of displayed for all to see.\" --Hildin, priest of Avacyn"
Shock: "\"The beauty of it is they never see it coming. Ever.\" --Razzix, sparkmage"
Shriek Raptor: "\"That's no glint hawk. The skies have changed for the worse.\" --Ria Ivor, White Sun partisan"
Siege Mastodon: "\"The walls of the wicked will fall before us. Ready the siege engines. We proceed to war!\" --General Avitora"
Sightless Ghoul: "It blindly marches on Thraben's gates, guided by its master's direful will."
Sigil of the Nayan Gods: "As the elves learned the hymns of angels, the knights learned the roars of titans."
Sign in Blood: "Little agonies pave the way to greater power."
Signal Pest: "It leaps from tree to tree, revealing the enemy's positions."
Silent Departure: "The same magic that lets geists pass through our realm can force them out of it."
Silklash Spider: "By the time the spider comes to slurp up its dinner, its victims have been partially dissolved by acidic silk."
Silver Knight: "Otaria's last defense against the wave of chaos threatening to engulf it."
Silverchase Fox: "\"Be careful in your hunt. The clever little creature can steal your wards and lead you right into the werewolf's den.\" --Britta, midwife of Gatstaf"
Silverclaw Griffin: "It patrols the grafs for miles around Thraben, ensuring that the unhallowed do not wake for long."
Silvercoat Lion: "\"In the wild, white fur like mine is an aberration. We lack natural camouflage, but the inability to hide encourages other strengths.\" --Ajani Goldmane"
Silverskin Armor: "Partisan spies warned that no armor would protect the body from Phyrexian infection. Neurok strategists took that as a challenge."
Simic Initiate: "Simic initiates begin their training as experimental subjects. Failures are flushed to the undersewers."
Simic Ragworm: "\"Infused with autochthon blood for size and hellion cells for speed, the ragworm is perfect for clearing the undergardens of both rats and vagrants.\" --Yolov, Simic bioengineer"
Skaab Goliath: "\"Three heads, six arms, and some armor grafts are better than . . . the normal numbers of those things.\" --Stitcher Geralf"
Skillful Lunge: "\"Valor is a currency of the living that serves us well.\" --Cosper Lowe of the Silbern Guard"
Skinrender: "\"Your creations are effective, Sheoldred, but we must unite the flesh, not merely flay it.\" --Elesh Norn, Grand Cenobite"
Skirk Drill Sergeant: "\"I order you to volunteer.\""
Skirk Outrider: "Once the goblins thought about it, they preferred being atop a slateback to being in front of, behind, or underneath one."
Skirsdag Flayer: "Certain initiates into the Skirsdag cult take a vow of blindness, pledging obedience to none but demonkind."
Sky Ruin Drake: "\"Hold up your spears. And try not to look like food.\" --Tarsa, Sea Gate sell-sword"
Sky-Eel School: "They swim on tides few can see, away from a threat few yet understand."
Skywinder Drake: "It's so light and fragile that it can glide where the air is thinnest."
Slagstorm: "\"As long as we have the will to fight, we are never without weapons.\" --Koth of the Hammer"
Slaughter Cry: "It's rather embarrassing to end up with your head mounted over his hearth."
Sleep: "\"I give them dreams so wondrous that they hesitate to return to the world of the conscious.\" --Garild, merfolk mage"
Slice in Twain: "\"The hypocrisy of these elves is thicker than steel--destroying ‘unnatural metal' with their own enchanted swords.\" --Kara Vrist, Neurok agent"
Slipstream Eel: "\"It's a fine way to travel, if you don't mind the smell.\""
Smallpox: "Take away a few things, and a rebellion may ensue. Take away everything, and the oppression will be accepted as fate."
Smokespew Invoker: "The Mirari festers in its flesh."
Smother: "\"I can't hear them scream, but at least I don't have to listen to them beg.\" --Phage the Untouchable"
Snapping Drake: "Foul-tempered, poorly trained, and mule-stubborn, the drake is the perfect test of the master's will."
Solemn Offering: "\"A relic donation is suggested.\" \"The suggestion is mandatory.\" --Temple signs"
Sorin's Thirst: "\"All your steel won't protect you if your will is weak.\""
Sorin's Vengeance: "\"Cherish these last moments. Though your miserable life has come to nothing, I have given it a magnificent end.\""
Soul Conduit: "\"You have an unhealthy attachment to your selfhood. I can help you with that.\" --Malcator, Executor of Synthesis"
Soul Parry: "\"I was called to this world of steel, and it will be my steel that answers.\" --Elspeth Tirel"
Soul Warden: "\"One does not question the size or shape of the grains of sand in an hourglass. Nor do I question the temperament of the souls under my guidance.\""
Soul's Attendant: "In truth, her own faith was gone, trodden in Ulamog's wake. She pantomimed the blessing in the hope that it would inspire others to continue to struggle."
Soul's Fire: "An avatar he sculpts of anger and flame."
Soulcage Fiend: "Vowing to free the souls of her children, Kastinne followed the tormentors into the ghastly network of caves below Stensia."
Soulless One: "\"Surrender your soul to me.\""
Spare from Evil: "\"As long as we can utter a prayer or lift a weapon, we have the power to fight back.\" --Thalia, Knight-Cathar"
Sparkmage Apprentice: "Sparkmages are performance artists of sorts, but pain is the price of admission."
Sparksmith: "\"If it didn't hurt, how would I know it worked?\""
Spectral Flight: "\"The church looks down on binding spirits into armor, but now I can look down on them.\" --Dierk, geistmage"
Spellskite: "\"Let's show Vorinclex that progress doesn't always need teeth or claws.\" --Malcator, Executor of Synthesis"
Spiked Baloth: "If a baloth isn't hungry, it's dead."
Spined Thopter: "\"I appreciate the depravity of noble designs turned to devious ends.\" --Tezzeret"
Spined Wurm: "\"They're as much like plants as animals. Leave them unchecked, and they'll choke out all other forms of life.\" --Hadi Kasten, Calla Dale naturalist"
Spire Serpent: "A mirror to draw its eye, a rod to rouse its rage, and a sword to break its bonds."
Spirit Mantle: "The shield of unimpeachable purity is as strong as any wrought on the anvil."
Spiteful Shadows: "\"Let us remind these human cattle why they fear the shadows of this world.\" --Aldreg, Skirsdag cultist"
Spitting Earth: "\"We were ready for an attack from the front, sides, or back--but the mage hit us from below.\" --Veteran soldier"
Spread the Sickness: "Life is ephemeral. Phyrexia is eternal."
Spurnmage Advocate: "\"Our unity humbles our foes.\""
Spurred Wolverine: "After a few painful experiences, goblins learned not to pick their noses around the beasts."
Stabbing Pain: "\"You can take the fight out of nearly any creature if you know where its soft spot is.\" --Guttor, flesh-warper"
Stampeding Rhino: "The quickest way to get through the jungle is to agitate a rhino and run in its wake."
Starlight Invoker: "The Mirari glows in her eyes."
Starved Rusalka: "\"No more wretched fate is there than to waste away. If you are slain, your ghost may at least avenge itself upon your killer. But what release is there for one slain by Time?\" --Ilromov, traveling storyteller"
Stasis Cell: "The Simic created the cells to preserve their experiments. The Azorius put the cells to use on the guilty."
Steel Sabotage: "\"You are hopelessly obsolete, my brothers. Come and join the Great Work.\" --Rhmir, Hand of the Augur"
Steppe Lynx: "Nothing quickens the predator's blood like the unfamiliar scents of new hunting grounds and the mewling cries of new prey."
Stingerfling Spider: "The juiciest prey is that which grows lazy, thinking itself beyond the reach of danger."
Stoic Champion: "His outer calm belies his inner fury."
Stone Golem: "The sculptor, like most artists, put his heart and soul in his work. But the newly awakened golem decided he wanted his creator's other, more tangible parts."
Stonehorn Dignitary: "It did not escape the ambassador's notice that the sound of war drums could also marshal the city to attention."
Stonewood Invoker: "The Mirari pulses in his veins."
Stormblood Berserker: "Blood is holy to those whose god is War."
Stormfront Pegasus: "Its hooves touch the earth only when a hero must rise."
Stratadon: "Designed like the gargadons of Keld--big and brutal."
Strength of Unity: "All Dominarians agreed on one thing: they would not go down without a fight."
Strider Harness: "Each journey begins with a single step--and sometimes ends with that single step as well."
Stromkirk Patrol: "\"You'd best move along, human. Our palates are far less discerning than our master's.\""
Sun Titan: "A blazing sun that never sets."
Sunblast Angel: "There may exist powers even greater than Phyrexia."
Supreme Inquisitor: "\"It's hard to fight on an empty mind.\""
Surrakar Banisher: "Surrakar grab things they don't want."
Surveilling Sprite: "Their natural curiosity, combined with a knack for trespassing, makes sprites excellent spies."
Sword of Vengeance: "When wielded by a true believer, it matters little whether the sword is a relic or a replica."
Sylvan Ranger: "\"Not all paths are found on the forest floor.\""
Sylvok Replica: "All the zeal of the Sylvok with only a trace of their conservancy."
Symbiotic Beast: "The insects found a meal in the carrion of the beast's prey. The beast found a spiffy new hairstyle."
Tangle Angler: "A plague on the curious."
Tangle Hulk: "\"A true Phyrexian predator. It will never know death, just as nature intended.\" --Vorinclex, Voice of Hunger"
Tangle Mantis: "The fiercest hunters in the Tangle don't seek out the mantises. They are the mantises."
Taste of Blood: "\"How blessed are some people, whose lives have no fears, no dreads, to whom sleep is a blessing that comes nightly, and brings nothing but sweet dreams.\" --Bram Stoker, Dracula"
Taunting Elf: "The safety of the village depends on the beast thinking with its stomach."
Temple of the False God: "Those who bring nothing to the temple take nothing away."
Teroh's Faithful: "The light of reason follows them even into battle."
Terrifying Presence: "Elmut had slaughtered vampires, slain werewolves, and destroyed hordes of zombies. Sadly, he never got over his fear of spiders."
Test of Faith: "Those who survive the test bear a mark of power anyone can recognize."
Thieving Magpie: "Other birds collect twigs for their nests. Magpies collect jewels for theirs."
Think Twice: "\"Either I know just the spell I need, or I'm about to.\""
Thought Scour: "\"As you inject the viscus vitae into the brain stem, don't let the spastic moaning bother you. It will soon become music to your ears.\" --Stitcher Geralf"
Thran Golem: "The golems of the ancient Thran still draw power in ways that baffle the artificers of today."
Threaten: "Goblins' motivational techniques are crude, but effective."
Thrive: "The most successful of Simic creations is cytoplasm, a living, symbiotic substance that feeds off genetic rhythms and strengthens its host in return."
Throne of Empires: "\"With this throne, unite your nation.\" --Throne inscription"
Thunder Strike: "Lightning reflexes, thunderous might."
Thunderbolt: "\"My next aerial design will use less metal.\" --Hadaken, alchemist of Nephalia"
Timbermaw Larva: "\"You can't trust your eyes. A tree might look healthy, but its insides tell a different tale.\" --Zahr Gada, Halimar expedition leader"
Timberwatch Elf: "Even through the Mirari's voice, the elves still hear the call of their kinship."
Timely Reinforcements: "The gods are not always kind, but they do have a soft spot for plucky underdogs."
Tine Shrike: "A new bird of prey--one that hunts sentience."
Tireless Missionaries: "If they succeed in their holy work, their order will vanish into welcome obscurity, for there will be no more souls to redeem."
Titanic Growth: "The pup looked over the treetops, eyeing the man who just yesterday had kicked her. Suddenly, her hunger was infused with pure delight."
Tome Scour: "Genius is overrated, especially when it's someone else's."
Torch Fiend: "Devils redecorate every room with fire."
Tormented Pariah: "\"Hey lads, the moon's rising. All the better to watch him beg for mercy.\""
Tormented Soul: "Those who raged most bitterly at the world in life are cursed to roam the nether realms in death."
Tormentor Exarch: "\"Tend the molten slag, or be the molten slag.\" --Urabrask's enforcer"
Totem-Guide Hartebeest: "The kor track hartebeests in hopes of finding magic to help fight the Eldrazi."
Tower Geist: "Jenrik's tower is served by those who once sought to enter it uninvited."
Tragic Slip: "Linger on death's door and risk being invited in."
Trained Orgg: "\"That arm's for bashin'. That one's for smashin'. That one's for scratchin'. And that one . . . I don't know what that one's for.\" --Orgg trainer"
Training Drone: "\"Vulshok flail, Viridian shield, loxodon blade . . . Tazzir, bring the Moriok hook and assemble the rookies.\" --Vy Covalt, Neurok agent"
Traitorous Blood: "\"I can make you dance to my tune like a puppet, your very blood eager to obey.\" --Olivia Voldaren"
Trapfinder's Trick: "\"At some point, every trapfinder will lose a hunk of flesh. It's just a question of how much--and whether it'll grow back.\" --Arhana, Kazandu trapfinder"
Travel Preparations: "Visiting a shrine at the start of a journey makes the traveler more likely to finish it."
Traveler's Amulet: "The rider set off into the eerie mist, swaddled in armor and laden with amulets."
Tree of Redemption: "The executioner's tree in Thraben Cathedral holds the power to absolve more than the souls of the hanged."
Trespassing Souleater: "\"We thank the souleaters for surveilling our lives that we may be preserved from our own ignorance.\" --Drones' hymn of gratitude"
Tribal Flames: "\"Fire is the universal language.\" --Jhoira, master artificer"
Tribute to Hunger: "Marella was delighted. The ball had attracted so many suitors for her daughter, including that handsome stranger. She wondered where the two were now . . . ."
True Conviction: "Dozens of spells known only to the Auriok elders were lost, but the next generation, galvanized by war, devised even more potent magic."
Trumpet Blast: "Keldon warriors don't need signals to tell them when to attack. They need signals to tell them when to stop."
Trusty Machete: "\"Until this expedition is done, that blade is your guardian, your liberator, and your best friend all rolled into one.\" --Yon Basrel, Oran-Rief survivalist"
Tumble Magnet: "Magnetic devices that keep massive golems and structures standing can also be used for the opposite purpose."
Turn the Tide: "\"Let their mindless armies come and face the might of genius.\" --Varil, Neurok partisan"
Turn to Frog: "\"Ribbit.\""
Turn to Slag: "\"If it wasn't a blackened, stinking, melted abomination before, it certainly is now.\" --Koth of the Hammer"
Ulamog's Crusher: "\"Whatever the Eldrazi's purpose is, it has nothing to do with something so insignificant as us.\" --Nirthu, lone missionary"
Unburial Rites: "All crave the Blessed Sleep. Few receive it."
Undead Executioner: "Heartless killer in life, brainless killer in death."
Unholy Strength: "\"Born under the moon, the second child will stumble on temptation and seek power in the dark places of the heart.\" --Codex of the Constellari"
Unnatural Predation: "\"Domination by the strongest--that is all that matters in the Tangle now.\" --Vorinclex, Voice of Hunger"
Unquestioned Authority: "\"Only the Ancestor should be revered.\" --Mystic heretic"
Unruly Mob: "\"Who says werewolves are the only ones who can hunt as a pack?\" --Kolman, elder of Gatstaf"
Unsummon: "\"It's nothing personal. I'd just prefer if you weren't.\" --Ashurel, voidmage"
Untamed Might: "\"Beasts kill for their very survival. If you would have their strength, you must know their desperation.\" --Konnos, Sylvok sage"
Urgent Exorcism: "\"To show geists pity is to prolong their agonies. Whether they know it or not, they seek the Blessed Sleep, and we are to give it to them.\" --Mikaeus, the Lunarch"
Vampire Interloper: "He listens to every heartbeat, deciding which one of hundreds he will stop."
Vapor Snag: "\"This creature is inadequate. Send it to the splicers for innovation.\" --Malcator, Executor of Synthesis"
Vastwood Gorger: "\"A long and difficult incision revealed that all vital organs are housed in the head, save for a long chain of stomachs, forty in all, leading from its throat to the end of the tail.\" --Mulak Ffar, Vastwood Biodiversity"
Vault Skirge: "From the remnants of the dead, Geth forged a swarm to safeguard his throne."
Vault Skyward: "\"The edges of the Quicksilver Sea run dark with the spread of the Mephidross. Two more aerial passes before I can be sure what I'm seeing . . .\" --Lafarius, Neurok sky agent"
Vectis Silencers: "Even on Esper, there are those who eschew the use of magic in favor of simpler methods."
Vedalken Anatomist: "\"Specimen 211 examination report. Observation: graft sublimation incomplete. Result: death. Prepare specimen 212.\""
Vedalken Infuser: "\"All plans begin as dreams. I intend to awaken them.\""
Vela the Night-Clad: "Vela snuffs out every trace of Krond's reign, leaving pure nightfall in her wake."
Vendetta: "\"Consider my debt to your kin paid in full.\" --Idrol, Guul Draz assassin"
Vengeful Vampire: "He wields the full power of wrath unfettered by the sympathies of a soul."
Veteran Armorsmith: "\"Courage is a proud and gleaming shield. It does not bend or hide from sight. To fight with courage, we must forge in steel.\""
Vigean Hydropon: "Fruits of magic, roots in science."
Village Bell-Ringer: "\"Priests, hunters, slayers--to arms! The enemy approaches!\""
Village Cannibals: "Some have endured the horrors of Innistrad by becoming the worst monsters of all."
Villagers of Estwald: "You can spot a werewolf-infested town by its lack of butcher shops."
Viridian Betrayers: "To secure a place in Phyrexia's ranks, they hunted their surviving kin."
Viridian Claw: "\"Phyrexians can't corrupt what they can't get close enough to touch.\""
Virulent Wound: "Sadly, the extent of Gerkk's healing knowledge was \"don't pick at it.\""
Viscera Seer: "In matters of life and death, he trusts his gut."
Vital Splicer: "\"For every one that falls, ten shall rise. The revelation of New Phyrexia is at hand.\" --Vorinclex, Voice of Hunger"
"Vitu-Ghazi, the City-Tree": "In the autumn, she casts her seeds across the streets below, and come spring, her children rise in service to the Conclave."
Vivisection: "Phyrexians research with the grace of surgeons and the finesse of butchers."
Voice of the Provinces: "Her horn is heard across Innistrad, lifting the hearts of the righteous."
Volcanic Dragon: "Sometimes an eruption in Shiv produces something more dangerous than a mere river of molten rock."
Volcanic Strength: "The mountains bend to no one."
Vulshok Heartstoker: "He fashions stirring words with as much passion as a smith fashioning a warhammer."
Vulshok Refugee: "\"I will carve my people's vengeance on the face of Phyrexia.\""
Vulshok Replica: "All the fury of the Vulshok with only a trace of their recklessness."
Wakedancer: "Hers is an ancient form of necromancy, steeped in shamanic trance and ritual that few skaberen or ghoulcallers comprehend."
Walking Corpse: "\"Is it hopeless? When wave upon wave of our dead return as mindless flesh-eaters to claw upon Thraben's walls? We're too busy cutting them down to indulge ourselves in such philosophical foppery.\" --Mikaeus, the Lunarch"
Wall of Frost: "\"I welcome it. The pasture is cleared of weeds and the wolves are frozen solid.\" --Lumi, goatherd"
Wall of Roots: "Sometimes the wise ones wove their magic into living plants; as the plant grew, so grew the magic."
Wall of Spears: "“A stick is your friend. A pointed stick is your good friend. An army of pointed sticks is your best friend.” -Onean sergeant"
Wall of Torches: "The foolish try to leap through the unlit spaces. The arrogant believe the fires harmless. The wise find a different door."
Wall of Vines: "Like all jungle plants, the vines must fight and claw for sunlight. Once their place is secured, they grow strong, sharp, and impenetrable."
Wandering Stream: "\"Dominaria touches us all.\" --Molimo, maro-sorcerer"
Wandering Wolf: "Humans still feared wolves, though no connection between them and the curse of lycanthropy had ever been proved."
War Priest of Thune: "\"The sacred might of Thune thunders in my soul.\""
War Report: "Underling Ethu's 263rd report read simply \"Yes, my lord. Overwhelmingly, my lord.\" This marked the end of the Mirran-Phyrexian War."
Warpath Ghoul: "Ghouls are often found skulking on the fringes of great battles, showing themselves only to snatch the wounded and weak, dragging their victims screaming into the shadows."
Waste Away: "Chainer's insanity touched nearly every living thing--including viruses."
Watchwolf: "Only in Ravnica do the wolves watch the flock."
Water Servant: "\"This creature has innate perceptiveness. It knows when to rise and when to vanish into the tides.\" --Jestus Dreya, Of Elements and Eternity"
Wave of Indifference: "\"Darius?\" \"Yeah?\" \"There's a goblin sneaking up on you.\" \"So?\" \"Just sayin'.\""
Wayfaring Giant: "Its stature and stride increase with each step it takes."
Welkin Guide: "\"Those talons really dig into your skin, but it's better than being dropped.\" --Rafiq of the Many"
Whipcorder: "His bolas whirl like galaxies, but it's his enemies who see stars."
Whipgrass Entangler: "\"Now that I have your attention, perhaps I can tell you of the Order.\""
Whispersilk Cloak: "Such cloaks are in high demand both by assassins and by those who fear them."
Wickerbough Elder: "\"Living scarecrows make a mockery of the natural order. Dead ones make fine hats.\""
Wild Guess: "No guts, no glory."
Wild Hunger: "Otto the Hunter was filled with many grand ambitions. The snake was filled only with Otto."
Wild Nacatl: "\"The Cloud Nacatl sit and think, a bunch of soft paws. We are the Claws of Marisi, stalking, pouncing, drawing blood.\""
Wildheart Invoker: "\"Life as we know it dangles on the brink of extinction. We must show the strength they would steal from us.\" --The Invokers' Tales"
Wind Drake: "A smaller cousin to the dragon, drakes are often seen at the side of powerful wizards who use them as airborne eyes and ears."
Windborne Charge: "The merfolk call the sky goddess Emeria. The kor call her Kamsa. The two races agree on little except that she offers many blessings to the faithful."
Wirewood Guardian: "Tall as a tree and probably related."
Withered Wretch: "Once it consecrated the dead. Now it desecrates them."
Wolfhunter's Quiver: "\"Steel in the heart, silver in the bow.\" --Wolfhunter's creed"
Woodland Sleuth: "\"Whatever did this is near. Death reversion has not yet occurred. Be alert!\""
Wreath of Geists: "Before you travel the woods of Kessig, first get permission from those who died trying."
Wring Flesh: "\"Don't blame me. You're the one walking around with skin.\" --Zul Ashur, lich lord"
Wurm's Tooth: "Jevna Nor lugged it around, bragging of his triumph over the wurm. Luckily, the tavern regulars didn't notice it was only a baby tooth."
Yavimaya Dryad: "The parched earth still shielded those few souls with the heart to call it home."
Yavimaya Wurm: "Anywhere else, colossal. In the forests of Yavimaya, commonplace."
Young Wolf: "The Ulvenwald makes no allowances for youth. Today's newborn is either tomorrow's hunter or tomorrow's lunch."
Zealous Inquisitor: "\"I only return what rightly belongs to another.\""
Zombie Goliath: "\"Removing the encumbrance of useless brain tissue grants several advantages: a slight increase in mobility, a response of revulsion and horror from the enemy, and, in the case of large specimens, room for passengers.\" --Zul Ashur, lich lord"
Zombie Infestation: "The nomads' funeral pyres are more practical than ceremonial."
Battle Hymn: "\"A church is just wood and walls. A congregation is the faithful praising the angels.\" --Kolman, elder of Gatstaf"
Grounded: "\"We've tracked Ludevic's monster across four provinces. When it lands, make sure it stays put.\" --Alena, trapper of Kessig, to Halana of Ulvenwald"
Scrapskin Drake: "\"The cathars killed my skaabs down below. Let's see how high their swords can reach.\" --Ludevic, necro-alchemist"
Spirit Away: "The fear of slipping from the geist's tenuous grip overwhelmed Tolo's joy at his first flight."
Fettergeist: "The choices of the living will tether them in death."
Midnight Duelist: "Avacyn's return did not rid him of his desire for revenge."
Scroll of Griselbrand: "Words no eyes should see, telling of things no sane mind could fathom."
Vanguard's Shield: "Wars are not fought on a single front."
Elite Inquisitor: "\"No matter how many I kill, there are always more to hunt. It makes me smile just to think about it.\""
Moonlight Geist: "Wails and whispers are the only weapons she has left."
Angelic Benediction: "\"Only the bravest are worthy of our blessing.\""
Erase: "\"Don't trust your eyes, for mages are skilled in deception. Trust only in your faith. It will wipe everything clean.\" --Lila, Erunian priest"
Aven Squire: "When the meek charge into battle, courage becomes infectious."
Touch of the Eternal: "\"Time is a vigilant tyrant, but there are those who have broken free of its gaze.\" --Laikas, Erunian monk"
Griffin Protector: "The drums of war stir the hearts of all who fight for righteousness."
Cloudshift: "\"Even storm clouds bow to worship Avacyn.\" --Elder Rimheit"
Battleflight Eagle: "Eagles make fine mounts, but they're too proud to carry anyone for long."
Burden of Guilt: "\"Grab an axe and defend the gate! Your despair is an extravagance we can ill afford.\" --Thalia, Knight-Cathar"
Cursebreak: "No longer the village pariah. No longer taunted and shamed. Sigrun was finally free."
Bar the Door: "\"It may not look like much, but it's a good old door with strong wards. It'll hold.\" --Olgard of the Skiltfolk"
Thraben Purebloods: "\"I've learned to trust my dogs' instincts. When they're calm, I'm calm. And when they get nervous, I get my crossbow.\" --Hinrik of House Cecani"
Vile Rebirth: "\"‘Here lies our beloved Gartu, the gentlest of all men.' Ooh, I love irony.\" --Jadar, ghoulcaller of Nephalia"
Moan of the Unhallowed: "For a ghoul, every village is a buffet and every disaster is a reunion."
Dark Favor: "When he began to curse what he held holy, his strength grew unrivaled."
Blood Artist: "\"Great art can never be created without great suffering.\""
Ravenous Rats: "Devouring books is only the beginning. The librarian's next."
Abattoir Ghoul: "Death took his humanity but not his skill with the knife."
Bloodhunter Bat: "It returns eager to share the feast of blood and gore with its ghoulish master."
Driver of the Dead: "Some vampires resorted to corpse trading after cathars burned their estates and drove them from their ancestral feeding grounds."
Markov Patrician: "Vampires of the Markov bloodline pride themselves on their exquisite taste in fashion, art, and \"wine of the vein.\""
Searchlight Geist: "It rises with the fall of darkness, seeking souls to extinguish."
Victim of Night: "\"Do not touch a drop. Not yet. I want to watch this so-called slayer's last crisis of faith.\" --Olivia Voldaren"
Public Execution: "Though the executioner did not speak, the villagers got the message."
Renegade Demon: "\"Have you ever cornered a wounded vampire? That's a walk in the cathedral garden in comparison.\" --Tristen, Cathar Marshal"
Knight of Infamy: "\"Your laws, like your bones, were made to be broken.\""
Servant of Nefarox: "\"My cause is power, and at the altar of power I will gladly forfeit my soul.\""
Harvester of Souls: "\"He is judge, jury, and executioner because he killed them all.\" --Bishop Cawle of Elgaud"
Grave Exchange: "\"It's a cold, dark journey either way.\" --Eruth of Lambholt"
Necrobite: "An undead snake doesn't bite in self-defense. It hungers as any zombie, never sated."
Mental Agony: "\"His mind is feeble. Feed him to the bats.\""
Unhallowed Pact: "Agreements with demons seldom end at the grave."
Barter in Blood: "\"We must all make sacrifices for the good of Innistrad.\" --Sorin Markov"
Vedalken Entrancer: "\"Don't get any ideas.\""
Mind Sculpt: "\"Your mind was a curious mix of madness and genius. I just took away the genius.\" --Jace Beleren"
Fog Bank: "\"The union of sea and sky makes a perfect cover.\" --Talrand, sky summoner"
Dreadwaters: "Stray into the Morkrut and it may rise to claim you."
Welkin Tern: "\"It preys on other birds. And drakelings. And drakes. Pretty much anything that crosses its flight path is fair game.\" --Amira, skycaptain of Thune"
Jace's Phantasm: "In the abstract memories of the Iquati, Jace found interesting ideas to improve upon."
Talrand's Invocation: "After Talrand conquered the depths of Shandalar, his ambitions drove him skyward, joined by servants whose drive and curiosity equaled his own."
Gryff Vanguard: "\"Ghouls smashed the door, but I heard the call of the gryffs and knew we were saved.\" --Ekka, shopkeeper of Hanweir"
Archaeomancer: "\"Words of power never disappear. They sleep, awaiting those with the will to rouse them.\""
Encrust: "\"Barnacles are the sea's final defense.\" --Garild, merfolk mage"
Ghostly Touch: "\"Geists wish to make themselves known. I'm merely the vessel for their efforts.\""
Faerie Invaders: "Small enough to penetrate the narrowest crack in a castle wall and numerous enough to hack apart a griffin."
Hydrosurge: "\"Thirsty?\" --Drunvalus, hydromancer"
Merfolk of the Pearl Trident: "\"The merfolk of the Pearl Trident have risen from the waves since the earliest days, at times allies to humans, other times enemies. Now their power is cresting again, and who can say which way the new tide will flow.\" --Kalis, Onean scholar"
Avacyn's Pilgrim: "\"Avacyn's protection is everywhere. From the holy church to the sacred glade, all that we see is under her blessed watch.\""
Somberwald Spider: "Stensian vampires encourage spiders near their manors so they can rob the webs."
Make a Wish: "In Gavony wishing is taken as a sign of weakness, yet the wells usually brim with silver."
Hollowhenge Scavenger: "After werewolves slaughtered the citizenry of Hollowhenge, other creatures moved in."
Scorned Villager: "\"My village's fear drove me into the wild . . .\""
Natural End: "The haunted blade shattered, and the geist drifted gratefully to the Blessed Sleep."
Timberland Guide: "\"Can you build a fire? Track a deer? Identify killer trees? Then you'll never survive Kessig without me.\""
Wildwood Geist: "The geists that dwell in the deep forests of Kessig are as untamable as the woods themselves."
Eaten by Spiders: "After sampling many victims, the spider developed a preference for the undead and their accoutrements."
Wolfir Avenger: "Released from a dark curse and bound to a higher calling."
Yeva's Forcemage: "\"Nature can't be stopped. It rips and tears at Ravnica's tallest buildings to claim its place in the sun.\""
Bond Beetle: "A beetle on your shoulder --Elvish expression meaning \"a blessing of luck\""
Primal Huntbeast: "\"To the unskilled, it appears as blurred patches of distorted light. Few have seen its true form.\" --Garruk Wildspeaker"
Mwonvuli Beast Tracker: "\"The more dangerous, the better.\""
"Yeva, Nature's Herald": "\"I can call an army to my side in the blink of an eye. Best not blink.\""
Roaring Primadox: "\"They're easy enough to find. Question is, are you sure you want to find one?\" --Juruk, Kalonian tracker"
Riot Devils: "Devils are demons' unearthly desires made flesh. Let loose on the world, they satisfy their mad craving for destruction in a whirlwind of chaos."
Ancient Grudge: "If there's anything a werewolf hates, it's a collar--especially Avacyn's Collar, the symbol of her church."
Pillar of Flame: "\"May the worthy spend an eternity in Blessed Sleep. May the wicked find the peace of oblivion.\""
Malicious Intent: "As peace returned to Thraben, some cathars made the mistake of letting down their guard."
Somberwald Vigilante: "He has nothing left but his resentment."
Gang of Devils: "\"Well, how could I know they'd explode?\" --Gregel, township militia"
Raging Poltergeist: "Some tried cremating their dead to stop the ghoulcallers. But the dead returned, furious about their fate."
Kessig Malcontents: "Discontent is a powerful weapon in the hands of a mob."
Riot Ringleader: "\"So the vampires like hot blood, do they? Let's see how they handle ours.\""
Kindled Fury: "\"Rage is a dangerous weapon. Your enemies will try to use your anger against you. Use it against them first.\" --Ajani Goldmane"
Chandra's Fury: "\"I asked if they wanted to do things the easy way. I meant easy for me.\""
Krenko's Command: "Goblins are eager to follow orders, especially when those orders involve stealing, hurting, annoying, eating, destroying, or swearing."
Wall of Fire: "Mercy is for those who keep their distance."
Arms Dealer: "\"Guaranteed to leave your enemies sufficiently stabbed, bitten, cleaved, or exploded.\" --Grezkrick's Emporium motto"
Craterize: "\"‘Utterly' is my favorite way to destroy something.\" --Chandra Nalaar"
Rummaging Goblin: "To a goblin, value is based on the four S's: shiny, stabby, smelly, and super smelly."
Searing Spear: "Sometimes you die a glorious death with your sword held high. Sometimes you're just target practice."
Smelt: "\"Looks like that wasn't darksteel after all.\" --Koth of the Hammer"
Cleaver Riot: "Measure once, cut twice."
Hunted Ghoul: "Even after Hanweir was saved, Gisa's lost ghouls would shamble through, still following the twisted orders of their imprisoned master."
Amass the Components: "\"I knew I'd find a use for all that newt spittle!\""
Essence Harvest: "Captain Lewenheart uncovered evidence of a demon cult among the clergy. The Skirsdag never gave him a chance to prove his case."
Alchemist's Apprentice: "Side effects may include foul odors, scalding steam, and spontaneous nonexistence."
Death Wind: "Leukin stared at the smoldering angel feathers. \"Run!\" he screamed to his patrol. \"We don't stand a chance!\""
Triumph of Cruelty: "\"I've seen corpses prettier than you, beastmage.\" --Liliana Vess"
Alchemist's Refuge: "Persecuted alchemists fled deep into Kessig's wilds, seeking solitude to continue their ghoulish craft."
Emancipation Angel: "\"You have done your best. I give you leave to rest.\""
Door to Nothingness: "Only a madman could create such a door. Only an imbecile would open it."
Mass Appeal: "\"We have emerged triumphant from the darkness. Let our hard-won wisdom guide us to prosperity.\""
Conjurer's Closet: "\"Tomorrow wears yesterday's face.\" --Kordel the Cryptic"
Ajani's Sunstriker: "\"Ajani goes where he is needed most and in his name we keep his lands safe.\""
War Falcon: "The falcon is the picture of nobility, maintaining a regal bearing even as it conducts the bloody business of war."
Tormod's Crypt: "Dominaria's most extravagant crypt nevertheless holds an empty grave."
Mindclaw Shaman: "Nicol Bolas gives power to those who will abuse it most."
Goblin Battle Jester: "Somehow goblins found a tactical advantage by sending a clown to war."
Healer of the Pride: "\"No life is without meaning. No living thing is too small to be strong.\""
Mark of the Vampire: "\"My ‘condition' is a trial. The weak are consumed by it. The strong transcend it.\" --Sorin Markov"
Veilborn Ghoul: "Liliana's voice carries far, reaching beyond the cold pall of death."
